text: Pranitha Subhash (born 17 October 1992) is an Indian actress and model. She works mainly in South Indian films, including Kannada, Telugu, Tamil and Malayalam movies. She has also acted in Hindi films. Pranitha was born in Bangalore, Karnataka, India. Her father is a physician and her mother is a gynecologist. She is their only child. ==Career== She began her acting career in 2010 with the Kannada film Porki opposite Darshan. She became more popular after acting in successful films like Baava (2010), Attarintiki Daredi (2013), Massu Engira Masilamani (2015) and Enakku Vaaitha Adimaigal (2017). In 2012, she acted in the Kannada film Bheema Theeradalli, which received critical acclaim. In 2021, she made her debut in Hindi cinema with the films Hungama 2 and Bhuj: The Pride of India. ==Personal life== Pranitha married businessman Nitin Raju on 30 May 2021. They have two children. She continues to act in films and is known for her work in Indian cinema. == External Links == * Pranitha Subhash at IMDb == Sources == Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Indian movie actors
